metadata.name: Stereo Print #135
metadata.description:
Generative audio painted on canvas. Tap to see and hear the composition in real time.

Stereo Print is my second collection in the paint-with-sound genre. Each mint has uniquely generated two-channel audio in the style of jazz, distortion, chimes, tones, space, or noise. The piece's visual texture is sourced directly from the audio signal. The raw waveforms are layered, masked, and transformed to produce the final composition.

Made with Web Audio and p5js. Idlebit, 2022.

metadata.name: RushGushBlush #122
metadata.description:
Let's celebrate #fxhashturnsone with a cascade of colors!

This is just my second release on fxhash and I couldn't be happier to dedicate this project, however simple, to this amazing community.

I could go on describing the details of this piece but honestly I just wanted to create something very colorful for the party, without putting too many hidden meanings! :)
(Or maybe not...)

Happy birthday fxhash!

---

80% of primary sales will be donated to the Processing Foundation and Save Pakistan.

---

There are 17 different palettes and 3 formats, hope you'll find a combination that makes you happy!
The texture might look weird in thumbnails, so I recommend opening the piece in full screen and/or download the png by pressing "s".

---

By Todemashi 2022
NFT License 2.0

### NOTES
Made with p5js.
This project uses fx(stdio) by @alt_escapism - https://altesc.art/stdio

metadata.name: Crude Acceptance #81
metadata.description:
It was there when we arrived
    No owners, no gatekeepers
    The opportunity to explore
    The chance to transform
    What we are
    What we see
    And a trace will came with us
    And that way it will multiply
    As long as we allow
    To leave here a part of us
    It will be there when we leave
    No owners, no gatekeepers
    But itself



  Controls
  Format:
  'f' - switch square/full screen format

  View:

  'Arrow Up/Down' - Decrease/Increase distance to origin
  'Mouse Drag' - View Rotation


  Export:
  'x' - show/hide export menu
  'm' - quick canvas save


Created with p5.js (Javascript + GLSL) by Victor Doval @vicdoval (2022)
Designed to be seen in Google Chrome 102.0.5005.63

metadata.name: fxhash x thi.ng project template #685
metadata.description:
THIS IS NOT AN ARTWORK (at least not intentional)!

This NFT acts as a donation/funding mechanism for a new project template Git repo, providing a compact, ready-to-go scaffolding for generative art projects aimed at the fx(hash) platform/marketplace.

https://github.com/thi-ng/fxhash-tpl

This template evolved over time and has served as basis for some of the author's own NFT projects (https://www.fxhash.xyz/u/toxi). The template is aimed at TypeScript (but can be easily adapted to plain JavaScript) and, at the time of writing, uses Vite as dev & build tool, ensuring an altogether great & speedy workflow with minimal fuzz.

(In the future, I'm aiming to provide an alternative version for more advanced hybrid projects using TypeScript, Zig (https://ziglang.org) and WebAssembly (https://webassembly.org/)...)

Framework agnostic

Even though several packages from the https://thi.ng/umbrella ecosystem are used to provide various essential overarching functionality, the template is organized in such a way that the main parts are completely framework-agnostic. You should be able to easily plug in your own toolkit of choice, however I cannot promise to provide support for this myself (though happy to accept PRs, also in terms of further docs, how-tos, guides etc.)

Example project

A tiny, fully documented throwaway example sketch is included, illustrating the following:

- Overall project structure & build commands
- FXhash related setup
- Static & dynamic configuration and state (re)initialization (via dependency graph)
- FXhash PRNG wrapper & utilities
- Canvas & SVG conversion/export/download
- 2D geometry creation, transformation & drawing
- Basic vector algebra example usage


Keyboard shortcuts

- space :  pause/play animation
- x : download canvas as PNG
- s : download SVG version

In case of doubt, it's this example project what is used here for minting. The funding, however, will be used for the further maintenance of both this project template and supporting my other open source work. 20% are also donated to the FXhash development team itself.

Thank you for your support! ðŸ™ðŸ˜

metadata.description:
Shapes, sand & distance. 

When rendering is done, press 'S' or click the canvas to export a png.
By default, it renders at 3000x3000.
To render at a different resolution WxW, add the URL parameter '?w=W'.

Made in JavaScript, no libraries
